er*innen des Bandes diskutieren diese europäischen und »westlichen« Praktiken der geschlechterpolitischen Behauptung, Visualisierung und Hervorhebung migrantisierter Anderer und machen ihre Konsequenzen in unterschiedlichen Räumen deutlich.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Nov 2021) 0aImmigranszGermanyxSocial conditions. 0aMarginality, SocialzGermany. 0aMinority womenzGermanyxSocial conditions. 0aMuslim womenzGermanyxSocial conditions. 0aRacismzGermany. 0aSexismzGermany. 0aWomen immigrantszGermanyxSocial conditions. 4aBildungssoziologie. 4aBildungswissenschaft. 4aErziehungswissenschaft. 4aFamiliensoziologie. 4aGender Studies. 4aGeschlecht. 4aMigration. 4aPolitikwissenschaft. 4aReligion. 4aSoziologie. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Gender Studies.2bisacsh  aEducation Studies.  aGender.  aMigration.  aPolitical Science.  aReligion.  aSociology of Education.  aSociology of Family.  aSociology.1 aCastro Varela, María do Mar, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHess, Sabine, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKarakayalı, Juliane, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKulaçatan, Meltem, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLingen-Ali, Ulrike, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLingen-Ali, Ulrike, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aMecheril, Paul, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMecheril, Paul, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aPritsch, Sylvia, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSabel, Anna, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSarfert, Nadine, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.g